<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A756A6FA39FE4C" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">- Disc of metathorax + propodeum not sculptured by strong transverse keels; transverse keels present only on posterior surface of propodeum; occasionally short keels are present on ground of median furrow................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F33FEBD48A756E9FA39FDE4" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A756E9FA39FE07" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A756E9FA39FE07" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">2. Vertex of head and metathorax + propodeum very shiny, smooth, unsculptured, except transverse striae on posterior surface of propodeum, metapleuron and occasionally mesopleuron...................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A756D3FA39FDE4" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" box="[151,1436,511,532]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A756D3FA39FDE4" box="[151,1436,511,532]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">- Vertex of head and metathorax + propodeum dull, granulated.................................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F33FEBD48A75531FA39FD7A" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A75531FA39FDBF" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A75531FA39FDBF" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
3. Median furrow of metathorax + propodeum less deep (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F33FEBD4AC15531FCF8FDC2" box="[753,861,541,562]" captionStart="PLATE 118" captionStartId="380.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[270,1325,235,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-91@380.[234,1353,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="380" captionText="PLATE 118. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view (from Olmi 1989b). B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view (from Olmi 1989b). C, E. Chelae (from Olmi 1984). D. Male genitalia (from Olmi 1984). A–C. Gonatopus borneanus, holotype. D. G. borneanus, paratype. E. G. insularis, holotype. Scale bar 0.75 mm for A, 0.15 mm for C, 0.18 mm for D and 0.14 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278786" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278786/files/figure.png" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">Plate 118B</figureCitation>
); lateral regions of scutum with one or two transverse keels (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F33FEBD48D95516FEF1FDBF" box="[233,340,570,591]" captionStart="PLATE 118" captionStartId="380.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[270,1325,235,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-91@380.[234,1353,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="380" captionText="PLATE 118. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view (from Olmi 1989b). B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view (from Olmi 1989b). C, E. Chelae (from Olmi 1984). D. Male genitalia (from Olmi 1984). A–C. Gonatopus borneanus, holotype. D. G. borneanus, paratype. E. G. insularis, holotype. Scale bar 0.75 mm for A, 0.15 mm for C, 0.18 mm for D and 0.14 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278786" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278786/files/figure.png" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">Plate 118A</figureCitation>
)......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F33FEBD4CE55516FA39FDBF" authority="(Olmi)" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[1237,1436,570,591]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="381" pageNumber="382" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borneanus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F33FEBD4CE55516FAF1FDBF" box="[1237,1364,570,591]" italics="true" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">G. borneanus</emphasis>
(Olmi)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A7557BFA39FD7A" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A7557BFA39FD7A" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
- Median furrow of metathorax + propodeum deeper (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F33FEBD4AD4557BFCF7FD9C" box="[740,850,599,620]" captionStart="PLATE 119" captionStartId="384.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[184,1432,233,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-74@384.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="384" captionText="PLATE 119. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view. B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view. C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Male genitalia. A–C. Gonatopus pajanensis (from Olmi 1989b). D, E. G. pyrillae (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.29 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278790/files/figure.png" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">Plate 119A</figureCitation>
); lateral regions of scutum with four transverse keels (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F33FEBD4D5C557BFEB0FD7A" captionStart="PLATE 119" captionStartId="384.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[184,1432,233,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-74@384.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="384" captionText="PLATE 119. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view. B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view. C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Male genitalia. A–C. Gonatopus pajanensis (from Olmi 1989b). D, E. G. pyrillae (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.29 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278790/files/figure.png" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">Plate 119C</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F33FEBD4CE45559FA39FD7A" authority="(Olmi)" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[1236,1436,629,650]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="381" pageNumber="382" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pajanensis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F33FEBD4CE45559FAF0FD7A" box="[1236,1365,629,650]" italics="true" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">G. pajanensis</emphasis>
(Olmi)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F33FEBD48A755BEFA39FD34" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A755BEFA39FD57" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" box="[151,1436,658,679]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A755BEFA39FD57" box="[151,1436,658,679]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
4. Antenna short, more thickened distally and with segment 9 slightly longer than broad................. 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F33FEBD4CD655BEFA39FD57" authority="(Olmi)" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[1254,1436,658,679]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="381" pageNumber="382" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F33FEBD4CD655BEFAF0FD57" box="[1254,1365,658,679]" italics="true" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">G. insularis</emphasis>
(Olmi)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F33FEBD48A75583FA39FD34" blockId="381.[151,1436,365,709]" box="[151,1436,687,709]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F33FEBD48A75583FA39FD34" box="[151,1436,687,709]" pageId="381" pageNumber="382">
- Antenna long, less thickened distally and with segment 9 about three times as long as broad............ 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F33FEBD4CDE559CFA39FD34" authority="(Mani)" baseAuthorityName="Mani" box="[1262,1436,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Lestodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="381" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrillae">
